  "active_lock_reason": null,
  "body": "Doing fuzz with int8 throws an exception. In the following example, the error happens as the _num variable in the fuzz receives the 128 value and can't be parsed to an int8.\r\n\r\n```solidity\r\n// myContract function    \r\nfunction setNum(int8 _num) external onlyOwner {\r\n        num = _num;\r\n    }\r\n\r\n// myContract test\r\n  function testSetNum(int8 num) public {\r\n        myContract.setNum(num);\r\n        ...\r\n    }\r\n```\r\n\r\nmanually taking the value of the fuzz revert and trying to cast it throws this error:\r\n\r\n```bash\r\nTypeError: Explicit type conversion not allowed from \"int_const 129\" to \"int8\".\r\n```",
